<task id="task_E68E2024B1F6403AAA1130A39B1D4DCD" xml:lang="en-us">
    <title>Deploying a Service Controller</title>
    <taskbody>
        <context>
            <p>After having implemented a service controller, you need to deploy it. You usually do this in the <codeph>app-domain</codeph> domain on the application server where you have installed APP.</p>
            <p>You can deploy a service controller in the following way using the standard utilities of the application server:</p>
            <ol compact="no">
                <li>You need an <codeph>.ear</codeph> or <codeph>.war</codeph> file with the code and resources of the service controller.</li>
                <li>Deploy the <codeph>.ear</codeph> or <codeph>.war</codeph> file of the service controller to the <codeph>app-domain</codeph> domain.</li>
                <!--li><b>When setting up the application server resources for APP</b> (see <xref
                        href="../../Shared/Installation/t_InstAppServer.xml"
                            />):<p>Before starting the setup, copy the <codeph>.ear</codeph> or <codeph>.war</codeph> file of the service controller to the <codeph>controller</codeph> subdirectory of <codeph>&lt;install_pack_dir>/domains/app_domain</codeph>. Be aware that the subdirectory must not contain more than one <codeph>.ear</codeph> or <codeph>.war</codeph> file. </p><p>Execute the <codeph>build-glassfish.xml</codeph> file in <codeph
                            audience="app"
                        >&lt;install_pack_dir&gt;/install</codeph> as follows:</p><codeblock>&lt;ANT_HOME&gt;/bin/ant -f build-glassfish.xml SETUP</codeblock><p>This command has the following results: </p><p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>The <codeph audience="app">app-domain</codeph> domain is created and started. </li>
                            <li>The settings and resources for APP are created in the application server.</li>
                            <li><ph audience="app"
                                    >APP</ph> (<codeph>oscm-app</codeph>) and the service controller are deployed to the <codeph
                                    audience="app">app-domain</codeph> domain.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </p></li-->
            </ol>
